Rapper Erhiga Agarivbie aka Erigga has reacted to the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission’s (EFCC) penalty for landlords who rent houses to internet fraudsters popularly called Yahoo Boys. The anti-graft agency recently warned landlords they risk serving a 15-year jail term if they rent their properties to Yahoo boys.   Ahmed Musa donates N100m to 5,000 widows, others in Plateau     How to check rising prices of diesel, cooking gas –…     Court declines request to reject Tinubu, Atiku as APC,…   The Commission made this known via its official Twitter handle where its legal and prosecution team will be discussing the topic: “Landlord: Give your house to Yahoo boys, spend 15 years in jail,” at 6pm, Wednesday, June 26; on Twitter Space. Pondering on the subject matter, Paper Boi wondered what ought to be the punishment for the crop of ‘corrupt’ leaders in the country. “Dem say 15 years imprisonment for landlord when rent house to yahoo boy but what about country when yahoo men dey rule?” Erigga tweeted.